
                                            The South African Weather Service says the storm will eventually move to the northern parts of Gauteng into Tshwane.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service is warning of flooding in parts of Gauteng on Monday evening as a thunderstorm  moves across the southern parts of the province. It says the storm will eventually move to the northern parts of Gauteng into Tshwane.  Motorists are warned to be extra vigilant on the roads. Forecaster Victoria Nurse said: “It is now moving through Vereeniging into Johannesburg and will eventually affect the northern parts of Gauteng, including Pretoria. We have sent out a warning for flooding associated with this type of thunderstorm.”